I am only reviewing this tavern as a restaurant because I only went there to eat and not to drink. To start off, the music was really loud. I could barely hear and communicate with the cashier/chef. The food is very cheap especially when you consider its location in Downtown Chicago. I got a double cheeseburger and it cost me only $5.99. The fries were slightly bigger than fries at other restaurants and they were made hot, fresh, and crispy. The cheeseburger though is nothing special. The bun was dry and I think they gave me more onions than beef. The burger was average at best. Considering the price they sell their burgers at, its not that bad. You get what you pay for, so the burger turning out to be average was not really all that surprising. All in all, the only thing above average about this restaurant is the fries, other than that the whole restaurant experience is average.

It's ok. Hard to hear with the bar music and the food was ok but cheap so I'd say it's at least worth the food experience. However, as a woman I would caution going in alone. I was there with my SIL and when I asked where the restroom was and someone pointed her to the right direction, some loud drunk dude (I assume a regular with how the whole bar addressed him), stood up like he was going to follow her and then sat down laughed and gestured his hand in the well known "just kidding" kind of way. Then as we were waiting for our order he just stood and stared at my SIL while she sat down and looked at her phone. I literally kept my eye on him the whole time we were there. The vibe was weird and I was on edge. Maybe he was joking, I don't know but these are the type of scenarios that are real for women everywhere. So if you're a woman I would caution not to venture here alone.
